abstract: Turkey’s state-run Anadolu Agency reports Turkish warplanes hit suspected Kurdish rebel targets in Hakkari Province near town of Daglica; airstrikes occurred after militant group Kurdistan Workers’ Party killed two soldiers in Sirnak Province and attacked military base.
lead_paragraph: Earlier, rebels killed two soldiers in Sirnak Province, the military said.

headline.print_headline: Europe; Turkey: Jets Strike Kurdish Rebels
